K8s --> containerization management tool or orchestration tool.

History of k8s: created by google in 2013 in go lng.
Free-open source platform.
In 2014, google donated to CNCF(Cloud Native Computing Foundation).
K8s --> cluster.
Cluster --> group of servers or group of nodes.
Node --> it's a vm.
Pod --> small deployable unit  -->  will manages the containers.




Kubernetes Architecture:

Cluster --> 1 master node, "n" worker nodes.

Master node --> control plane, brain of cluster--> controlls entire cluster.
	1. API server --> responsible for managing incoming traffic towards application/cluster.
	Customer request --> API server.
	Handles api calls, entire process.
	Create pods, perform autoscaling -->api server.
	Stores info in ETCD.
	
	2. ETCD: stores the info of the deployment in cluster --> pod, services, deployments.
	Directory inside linux terminal. 
	/ -->root dir . /etc --> we are storing info related deployment 
/ --> ls,  etc


	3. Scheduler: kube scheduler or default scheduler.
	Customer request ---> API server --> Scheduler.
	Pod --> API server --> scheduler.
	Decides where pod has to be created.
	
	
Worker Node:
	1. Kubelet: responsible for communication to master node. 
         Acts like agent, tell all the info in worker to master node.
	1. Kubeproxy --> most important component in the cluster.
	Container communication . Like a networking component.
	IP Address, exposing app to internet.
	2. Container run-time: responsible for pulling image from ECR or docker hub.
	Manage the container life cycle.
	3. Pod -->  where deployment is done. Automatically create required things.
